{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1175,"text":"Cities are like siblings\nin a large polygamous family."},{"time":6373,"text":"Each one has a unique personality\nand is headed in a distinct direction."},{"time":11209,"text":"But they all have somewhat shared origins."},{"time":14677,"text":"Sometimes I think postcolonial cities\nare like the children"},{"time":17748,"text":"of the two least-favorite wives,"},{"time":19471,"text":"who are constantly being asked,"},{"time":21079,"text":"\"Ah, why can't you be\nmore like your sister?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":23306,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":26281,"text":"The \"why\" of cities is largely the same,\nno matter where they are:"},{"time":30492,"text":"an advantageous location that makes\ntrade and administration possible;"},{"time":34636,"text":"the potential for scalable opportunities"},{"time":36852,"text":"for the skilled and unskilled alike;"},{"time":39253,"text":"a popular willingness\nto be in constant flux"},{"time":42296,"text":"and, of course, resilience."},{"time":44767,"text":"The \"how\" of cities, however,\nis a whole other story."},{"time":48175,"text":"How are they run?"},{"time":49902,"text":"How do they grow?"},{"time":51719,"text":"How do they decide who belongs\nand who doesn't?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":55751,"text":"Lagos is my home."},{"time":58540,"text":"You can always find the Nigerians"},{"time":60235,"text":"by following the noise\nand the dancing, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":62489,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":63649,"text":"Like any major city,\nthat place is a lot of things,"},{"time":67513,"text":"many of which are highly contradictory."},{"time":70550,"text":"Our public transportation\ndoesn't quite work,"},{"time":72670,"text":"so we have these privately owned\nbright yellow buses"},{"time":75849,"text":"that regularly cause accidents."},{"time":78735,"text":"Luxury car showrooms line badly maintained\nand often flooded roads."},{"time":83738,"text":"Street evangelism is only\nslightly less ubiquitous"},{"time":86581,"text":"than street harassment."},{"time":88705,"text":"Sex workers sometimes\nhave two degrees, a bank job"},{"time":91951,"text":"and a prominent role in church."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93783,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":94811,"text":"On any given day,"},{"time":95997,"text":"there can be either a party\nor a burned body"},{"time":99350,"text":"in the middle of a street."}]},{"cues":[{"time":102724,"text":"There is so much that is possible in Lagos"},{"time":105529,"text":"and so much that isn't,"},{"time":106743,"text":"and very often the difference\nbetween possibility and impossibility"},{"time":109980,"text":"is simply who you are,"},{"time":111618,"text":"and if you're lucky enough,\nwho you're connected to."},{"time":114852,"text":"Belonging in Lagos is a fluid concept"},{"time":117065,"text":"determined by ethnic origin,\nsexual orientation, gender,"},{"time":121217,"text":"but most visibly and often most violently,"},{"time":124576,"text":"class."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126492,"text":"Before Nigeria became a country,"},{"time":129117,"text":"fisherpeople from the inland creeks\nstarted to come down the Lagos lagoon"},{"time":133052,"text":"and establish villages along the coast."},{"time":136020,"text":"About 60 years later, my grandfather,\nOludotun Adekunle Kukoyi,"},{"time":140478,"text":"also arrived in Lagos."},{"time":142667,"text":"Like me, he was an alumnus\nof the University of Ibadan,"},{"time":146107,"text":"a young member of the educated elite\nin the independence era."},{"time":150262,"text":"Over time, he built an illustrious career\nas a land surveyor,"},{"time":153879,"text":"mapping out now-bustling neighborhoods"},{"time":155969,"text":"when they were just waist-high wild grass."},{"time":159353,"text":"He died when I was nine."},{"time":160783,"text":"And by that time, my family,\nlike the families of those fisherpeople,"},{"time":164594,"text":"knew Lagos as home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168133,"text":"Among the Yoruba, we have a saying,"},{"time":170388,"text":"\"Èkó gb’olè, ó gb’ọ̀lẹ,\""},{"time":172882,"text":"which can be translated to mean\nthat Lagos will welcome anyone."},{"time":177517,"text":"But that saying is becoming\nless and less true."},{"time":180964,"text":"Many Lagosians, including\nthe descendants of those fisherpeople"},{"time":184133,"text":"who arrived generations\nbefore my grandfather,"},{"time":186509,"text":"are now being pushed out"},{"time":188247,"text":"to make room for an emergent city"},{"time":189974,"text":"that has been described\nas \"the new Dubai.\""},{"time":193501,"text":"You see, Lagos inspires big dreams,\neven in its leaders,"},{"time":197631,"text":"and successive governments\nhave declared aspirations"},{"time":200339,"text":"towards a megacity\nwhere poverty does not exist."},{"time":204213,"text":"Unfortunately, instead of focusing\non the eradication of poverty"},{"time":207790,"text":"as you would expect,"},{"time":209317,"text":"the strategy of choice focuses\non eliminating the poor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215239,"text":"Last October, the Governor announced plans"},{"time":217399,"text":"to demolish every single\nwaterfront settlement in Lagos."},{"time":221883,"text":"There are more than 40\nof these indigenous communities"},{"time":224462,"text":"all over the city,"},{"time":225648,"text":"with over 300,000 people living in them."},{"time":228803,"text":"Otodo Gbame,"},{"time":230451,"text":"a hundred-year-old fishing village"},{"time":232441,"text":"with a population about\nthree-quarters that of Monaco"},{"time":235399,"text":"and similar potential\nfor beachfront luxury --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":238060,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":239117,"text":"was one of the first to be targeted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242693,"text":"I first heard of Otodo Gbame\nafter the demolition started."},{"time":246835,"text":"When I visited in November 2016,\nI met Magdalene Aiyefoju."},{"time":252123,"text":"She is a now-homeless woman"},{"time":253763,"text":"whose surname means, \"the world is blind.\""},{"time":257521,"text":"Magdalene's son Basil\nwas one of over 20 people"},{"time":261436,"text":"who were shot, drowned"},{"time":263285,"text":"or presumed dead in that land grab."},{"time":267632,"text":"Standing outside her shelter,\nI saw the two white-sand football fields"},{"time":271165,"text":"where Basil used to play."},{"time":273650,"text":"Spread all around us were the ruins\nof schools, churches,"},{"time":277313,"text":"a primary health center, shops,"},{"time":279457,"text":"thousands of homes."},{"time":281892,"text":"Young children enthusiastically helped\nto put up shelters,"},{"time":285405,"text":"and about 5,000 of the residents,\nwith nowhere else to go,"},{"time":288484,"text":"simply stayed put."},{"time":290838,"text":"And then in April,"},{"time":292953,"text":"state security personnel came back."},{"time":296229,"text":"This time, they cleared\nthe community out completely,"},{"time":299734,"text":"with beatings, bullets and fire."},{"time":303967,"text":"As I speak, there are construction crews\npreparing Otodo Gbame's beaches"},{"time":308477,"text":"for anyone who can afford\na multi-million-dollar view."},{"time":312222,"text":"The new development\nis called \"Periwinkle Estate.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":318388,"text":"Forced evictions are incredibly violent\nand, of course, unconstitutional."},{"time":323303,"text":"And yet, they happen so often\nin so many of our cities,"},{"time":326620,"text":"because the first thing we are taught\nto forget about poor people"},{"time":330389,"text":"is that they are people."},{"time":332592,"text":"We believe that a home is a thing\na person absolutely has a right to,"},{"time":335999,"text":"unless the person is poor\nand the home is built a certain way"},{"time":338997,"text":"in a certain neighborhood."},{"time":340891,"text":"But there is no single definition\nof the word \"home.\""},{"time":345450,"text":"After all, what is a slum\nbesides an organic response"},{"time":348715,"text":"to acute housing deficits\nand income inequality?"},{"time":352811,"text":"And what is a shanty if not a person\nmaking a home for themselves"},{"time":356018,"text":"against all odds?"},{"time":359195,"text":"Slums are an imperfect housing solution,"},{"time":361731,"text":"but they are also prime examples\nof the innovation, adaptability"},{"time":365448,"text":"and resilience at the foundation --"},{"time":368198,"text":"and the heart --"},{"time":369609,"text":"of every functional city."},{"time":372483,"text":"You don't need to be the new Dubai"},{"time":374858,"text":"when you're already Lagos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377549,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":384951,"text":"We have our own identity,"},{"time":387021,"text":"our own rhythm,"},{"time":388745,"text":"and as anyone who knows\nLagos can tell you,"},{"time":391064,"text":"poor Lagosians are very often\nthe source of the city's character."},{"time":395108,"text":"Without its poor, Lagos would not\nbe known for its music"},{"time":397881,"text":"or its endless energy"},{"time":399183,"text":"or even the fact that you can buy\nan ice cold drink or a puppy"},{"time":402856,"text":"through your car window."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404283,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":408399,"text":"The conditions that cause us\nto define certain neighborhoods as slums"},{"time":411844,"text":"can be effectively improved,"},{"time":413839,"text":"but not without recognizing\nthe humanity and the agency"},{"time":416926,"text":"of the people living in them."},{"time":419192,"text":"In Lagos, where public goods\nare rarely publicly available,"},{"time":422242,"text":"slum dwellers are often at the forefront\nof innovating solutions."},{"time":426640,"text":"After being disconnected\nfrom the grid for months"},{"time":429126,"text":"because the power company\ncouldn't figure out how to collect bills,"},{"time":432415,"text":"one settlement designed a system\nthat collectivized remittances"},{"time":435900,"text":"and got everyone cheaper rates\ninto the bargain."},{"time":439668,"text":"Another settlement created\na reform program"},{"time":441838,"text":"that hires local bad boys as security."},{"time":444616,"text":"They know every trick and every hideout,"},{"time":446766,"text":"so now troublemakers are more likely\nto get caught and reported to police"},{"time":450220,"text":"and fewer of the youth end up\nengaging in criminal activity."},{"time":454266,"text":"Yet another settlement recently completed"},{"time":456457,"text":"a flood-safe, eco-friendly\ncommunal toilet system."},{"time":460266,"text":"Models like these are being\nadopted across Lagos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464444,"text":"Informal settlements are incorrectly\nnamed as the problem."},{"time":468554,"text":"In fact, the real problems\nare the factors that create them,"},{"time":472003,"text":"like the entrenchment of poverty,"},{"time":473960,"text":"social exclusion"},{"time":475179,"text":"and state failures."},{"time":477386,"text":"When our governments\nframe slums as threats"},{"time":480032,"text":"in order to justify violent land grabs\nor forced evictions,"},{"time":482946,"text":"they're counting on those of us\nwho live in formal housing"},{"time":485935,"text":"to tacitly and ignorantly agree with them."},{"time":490635,"text":"Rather, we must remind them"},{"time":492677,"text":"that governments exist to serve\nnot only those who build"},{"time":495322,"text":"and live in luxury homes,"},{"time":496849,"text":"but also those who clean and guard them."},{"time":500223,"text":"Our --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":501406,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":505805,"text":"our realities may differ,"},{"time":508041,"text":"but our rights don't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512121,"text":"The Lagos state government,"},{"time":513818,"text":"like far too many on our continent,"},{"time":515765,"text":"pays lip service to ideas of inclusion,"},{"time":518462,"text":"while acting as though\nprogress can only be achieved"},{"time":521533,"text":"by the erasure, exploitation\nand even elimination of groups"},{"time":524989,"text":"it considers expendable."},{"time":527898,"text":"People living with disabilities\nwho hawk or beg on Lagos streets"},{"time":531399,"text":"are rounded up, extorted"},{"time":533618,"text":"and detained."},{"time":535335,"text":"Women in low-income\nneighborhoods are picked up"},{"time":537597,"text":"and charged with prostitution,"},{"time":539116,"text":"regardless of what they actually\ndo for a living."},{"time":542024,"text":"Gay citizens are scapegoated\nto distract from real political problems."},{"time":547931,"text":"But people, like cities, are resilient,"},{"time":552092,"text":"and no amount of legislation\nor intimidation or violence"},{"time":555521,"text":"can fully eliminate any of us."},{"time":558308,"text":"Prostitutes, women\nand women who work as prostitutes"},{"time":561970,"text":"still haven't gone extinct,"},{"time":563505,"text":"despite centuries of active suppression."},{"time":566894,"text":"Queer Africans continue to exist,"},{"time":569549,"text":"even though queerness is now criminalized\nin most parts of the continent."},{"time":573358,"text":"And I'm fairly certain that poor people\ndon't generally tend to just disappear"},{"time":577931,"text":"because they've been stripped\nof everything they have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581435,"text":"We are all already here,"},{"time":584896,"text":"and that answers the question"},{"time":587159,"text":"of whether or not we belong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591764,"text":"When those fisherpeople\nstarted to sail down the lagoon"},{"time":594902,"text":"in search of new homes,"},{"time":596361,"text":"it could not have occurred to them"},{"time":598448,"text":"that the city that would\nrise up around them"},{"time":600596,"text":"would one day insist\nthat they do not belong in it."},{"time":604825,"text":"I like to believe that my grandfather,"},{"time":607041,"text":"in mapping new frontiers for Lagos,"},{"time":608930,"text":"was trying to open it up"},{"time":610865,"text":"to make room for other people\nto be welcomed by the city"},{"time":613903,"text":"in the same way that he was."},{"time":616728,"text":"On my way here, my grandma called me"},{"time":619597,"text":"to remind me how proud she was,"},{"time":622358,"text":"how proud [my grandfather]\nand my mother would have been."},{"time":625735,"text":"I am their dreams come true."},{"time":629463,"text":"But there is no reason why their dreams --\nor mine, for that matter --"},{"time":634481,"text":"are allowed to come true"},{"time":635877,"text":"while those of others\nare turned to nightmares."},{"time":639300,"text":"And lest we forget:"},{"time":641384,"text":"the minimum requirement for a dream"},{"time":644331,"text":"is a safe place to lay your head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":649808,"text":"It is too late now for Basil,"},{"time":652545,"text":"but not for Magdalene,"},{"time":654468,"text":"not for the hundreds of thousands,"},{"time":656431,"text":"the millions still under threat in Lagos"},{"time":658849,"text":"or any of our cities."},{"time":661368,"text":"The world does not have to remain blind"},{"time":664218,"text":"to the suffering that is created\nwhen we deny people's humanity,"},{"time":668671,"text":"or even to the incredible potential\nfor growth that exists"},{"time":671985,"text":"when we recognize and value\nall contributions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677379,"text":"We must hold our governments"},{"time":680018,"text":"and ourselves"},{"time":681747,"text":"accountable"},{"time":683191,"text":"for keeping our shared cities safe\nfor everyone in them,"},{"time":688092,"text":"because the only cities worth building --"},{"time":690305,"text":"indeed, the only futures\nworth dreaming of --"},{"time":694287,"text":"are those that include all of us,"},{"time":697009,"text":"no matter who we are"},{"time":699286,"text":"or how we make homes for ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":702459,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703671,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}